88 /** Cancel a call to a submodule
89  *
90  * @param[in] mctx UNUSED.
91  * @param[in] request The current request.
92  * @param[in] rctx the eap_session_t
93  * @param[in] action to perform.
94  */
95 static void mod_signal(UNUSED module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request, UNUSED void *rctx,
96  fr_state_signal_t action)
97 {
98  eap_session_t *eap_session = eap_session_get(request->parent);
99 
100  if (action != FR_SIGNAL_CANCEL) return;
101 
102  RDEBUG2("Request cancelled - Destroying session");
103 
104  TALLOC_FREE(eap_session->opaque);
105 }

107 /** Warn the user that the rcode they provided is being ignored in this section
108  *
109  */
110 static inline void section_rcode_ignored(request_t *request)
111 {
112  switch (request->rcode) {
113  case RLM_MODULE_USER_SECTION_REJECT:
114  RWDEBUG("Ignoring rcode (%s)",
115  fr_table_str_by_value(rcode_table, request->rcode, "<invalid>"));
116  break;
117 
118  default:
119  break;
120  }

123 /** Trigger a state transition to FAILURE-NOTIFICATION if the section returned a failure code
124  *
125  */
126 #define section_rcode_process(_p_result, _inst, _request, _eap_session, _eap_aka_sim_session) \
127 { \
128  if (after_authentication(_eap_aka_sim_session)) { \
129  switch ((_request)->rcode) { \
130  case RLM_MODULE_REJECT: \
131  case RLM_MODULE_DISALLOW: \
132  eap_aka_sim_session->failure_type = FR_NOTIFICATION_VALUE_TEMPORARILY_DENIED; \
133  return common_failure_notification_enter(_p_result, _inst, _request, _eap_session); \
134  case RLM_MODULE_NOTFOUND: \
135  eap_aka_sim_session->failure_type = FR_NOTIFICATION_VALUE_NOT_SUBSCRIBED; \
136  return common_failure_notification_enter(_p_result, _inst, _request, _eap_session); \
137  case RLM_MODULE_INVALID: \
138  case RLM_MODULE_FAIL: \
139  eap_aka_sim_session->failure_type = FR_NOTIFICATION_VALUE_GENERAL_FAILURE_AFTER_AUTHENTICATION;\
140  return common_failure_notification_enter(_p_result, _inst, _request, _eap_session); \
141  default: \
142  break; \
143  } \
144  } else { \
145  switch ((_request)->rcode) { \
146  case RLM_MODULE_USER_SECTION_REJECT: \
147  REDEBUG("Section rcode (%s) indicates we should reject the user", \
148  fr_table_str_by_value(rcode_table, request->rcode, "<INVALID>")); \
149  return common_failure_notification_enter(_p_result, _inst, _request, _eap_session); \
150  default: \
151  break; \
152  } \
153  } \
154 }

156 /** Sync up what identity we're requesting with attributes in the reply
157  *
158  */
159 static bool identity_req_set_by_user(request_t *request, eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session)
160 {
161  fr_pair_t *vp;
162  fr_cursor_t cursor;
163  bool set_by_user = false;
164 
165  /*
166  * Check if the user included any of the
167  * ID req attributes. If they did, use
168  * them to inform what we do next, and
169  * then delete them so they don't screw
170  * up any of the other code.
171  */
172  for (vp = fr_cursor_init(&cursor, &request->reply_pairs);
173  vp;
174  vp = fr_cursor_next(&cursor)) {
175  if (vp->da == attr_eap_aka_sim_permanent_id_req) {
176  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_PERMANENT_ID_REQ;
177  found:
178  set_by_user = true;
179  RDEBUG2("Previous section added &reply.%pP, will request additional identity", vp);
180  fr_cursor_free_item(&cursor);
181  }
182  else if (vp->da == attr_eap_aka_sim_fullauth_id_req) {
183  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_FULLAUTH_ID_REQ;
184  goto found;
185  }
186  else if (vp->da == attr_eap_aka_sim_any_id_req) {
187  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_ANY_ID_REQ;
188  goto found;
189  }
190  }
191 
192  return set_by_user;
193 }

195 /** Based on the hint byte in the identity, add &Identity-Type and &Method-Hint attributes
196  *
197  */
198 static void identity_hint_pairs_add(fr_aka_sim_id_type_t *type_p, fr_aka_sim_method_hint_t *method_p,
199  request_t *request, char const *identity)
200 {
201  fr_aka_sim_id_type_t type;
202  fr_aka_sim_method_hint_t method;
203 
204  /*
205  * Process the identity that we received.
206  */
207  if (fr_aka_sim_id_type(&type, &method,
208  identity, talloc_array_length(identity) - 1) < 0) {
209  RPWDEBUG2("Failed parsing identity, continuing anyway");
210  }
211 
212  /*
213  * Map the output from the generic ID parser
214  * function to specific EAP-AKA internal
215  * attributes in the subrequest.
216  */
217  if (type != AKA_SIM_ID_TYPE_UNKNOWN) {
218  fr_pair_t *vp = NULL;
219 
220  MEM(pair_update_request(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_identity_type) >= 0);
221  switch (type) {
222  case AKA_SIM_ID_TYPE_PERMANENT:
223  vp->vp_uint32 = FR_IDENTITY_TYPE_VALUE_PERMANENT;
224  break;
225 
226  case AKA_SIM_ID_TYPE_PSEUDONYM:
227  vp->vp_uint32 = FR_IDENTITY_TYPE_VALUE_PSEUDONYM;
228  break;
229 
230  case AKA_SIM_ID_TYPE_FASTAUTH:
231  vp->vp_uint32 = FR_IDENTITY_TYPE_VALUE_FASTAUTH;
232  break;
233 
234  default:
235  fr_assert(0);
236  }
237  }
238 
239  /*
240  * Map the output from the generic ID parser
241  * function to specific EAP-AKA internal
242  * attributes in the subrequest.
243  */
244  if (method != AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_UNKNOWN) {
245  fr_pair_t *vp = NULL;
246 
247  MEM(pair_update_request(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_method_hint) >= 0);
248  switch (method) {
249  case AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_AKA_PRIME:
250  vp->vp_uint32 = FR_METHOD_HINT_VALUE_AKA_PRIME;
251  break;
252 
253  case AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_AKA:
254  vp->vp_uint32 = FR_METHOD_HINT_VALUE_AKA;
255  break;
256 
257  case AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_SIM:
258  vp->vp_uint32 = FR_METHOD_HINT_VALUE_SIM;
259  break;
260 
261  default:
262  fr_assert(0);
263  }
264  }
265 
266  if (type_p) *type_p = type;
267  if (method_p) *method_p = method;
268 }

285 /** Add an Identity Request attribute to the reply
286  *
287  * Verify the progression of identity requests is valid.
288  *
289  * @param[in] request The current request.
290  * @param[in] eap_aka_sim_session The current eap_aka_sim_session.
291  * @return
292  * - 0 on success.
293  * - -1 on failure (progression of identities was not valid).
294  */
295 static int identity_req_pairs_add(request_t *request, eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session)
296 {
297  fr_pair_t *vp;
298 
299  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->id_req) {
300  case AKA_SIM_ANY_ID_REQ:
301  if (eap_aka_sim_session->last_id_req != AKA_SIM_NO_ID_REQ) {
302  id_out_of_order:
303  REDEBUG("Cannot send %s, already sent %s",
304  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_aka_sim_id_request_table, eap_aka_sim_session->id_req, "<INVALID>"),
305  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_aka_sim_id_request_table, eap_aka_sim_session->last_id_req, "<INVALID>"));
306  return -1;
307  }
308  MEM(pair_add_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_any_id_req) >= 0);
309  vp->vp_bool = true;
310  break;
311 
312  case AKA_SIM_FULLAUTH_ID_REQ:
313  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->last_id_req) {
314  case AKA_SIM_NO_ID_REQ: /* Not sent anything before */
315  case AKA_SIM_ANY_ID_REQ: /* Last request was for any ID, but the re-auth ID was bad */
316  break;
317 
318  default:
319  goto id_out_of_order;
320  }
321  MEM(pair_add_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_fullauth_id_req) >= 0);
322  vp->vp_bool = true;
323  break;
324 
325  case AKA_SIM_PERMANENT_ID_REQ:
326  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->last_id_req) {
327  case AKA_SIM_NO_ID_REQ: /* Not sent anything before */
328  case AKA_SIM_ANY_ID_REQ: /* Last request was for any ID, but the re-auth ID was bad */
329  case AKA_SIM_FULLAUTH_ID_REQ: /* ...didn't understand the pseudonym either */
330  break;
331 
332  default:
333  goto id_out_of_order;
334  }
335  MEM(pair_add_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_permanent_id_req) >= 0);
336  vp->vp_bool = true;
337  break;
338 
339  default:
340  fr_assert(0);
341  }
342 
343  return 0;
344 }

346 /** Copy the incoming identity to the permanent identity attribute
347  *
348  * If the incoming ID really looks like a permanent ID, and we were
349  * told it was a permanent ID, then (optionally) trim the first byte
350  * to form the real permanent ID.
351  *
352  * Otherwise copy the entire incoming Identity to the
353  * &session-state.Permanent-Identity attribute.
354  *
355  * @param[in] request The current request.
356  * @param[in] in current identity.
357  * @param[in] eap_type The current eap_type.
358  * @param[in] strip_hint Whether to strip the hint byte off the permanent identity
359  */
360 static int identity_to_permanent_identity(request_t *request, fr_pair_t *in, eap_type_t eap_type, bool strip_hint)
361 {
362  fr_aka_sim_id_type_t our_type;
363  fr_aka_sim_method_hint_t our_method, expected_method;
364  fr_pair_t *vp;
365 
366  if (in->vp_length == 0) {
367  RDEBUG2("Not processing zero length identity");
368  return -1;
369  }
370 
371  /*
372  * Not requested to strip hint, don't do anything
373  * fancy, just copy Identity -> Permanent-Identity.
374  */
375  if (!strip_hint) {
376  MEM(fr_pair_update_by_da(request->state_ctx, &vp,
377  &request->state, attr_eap_aka_sim_permanent_identity) >= 0);
378  fr_pair_value_bstrndup(vp, in->vp_strvalue, in->vp_length, true);
379  return 0;
380  }
381 
382  switch (eap_type) {
383  case FR_EAP_METHOD_SIM:
384  expected_method = AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_SIM;
385  break;
386 
387  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA:
388  expected_method = AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_AKA;
389  break;
390 
391  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME:
392  expected_method = AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_AKA_PRIME;
393  break;
394 
395  default:
396  return -1;
397  }
398 
399  /*
400  * First, lets see if this looks like an identity
401  * we can process.
402  *
403  * For now we allow all permanent identities no
404  * matter what EAP method.
405  *
406  * This is because we could be starting a different
407  * EAP method to the one the identity hinted,
408  * but we still want to strip the first byte.
409  */
410  if ((fr_aka_sim_id_type(&our_type, &our_method, in->vp_strvalue, in->vp_length) < 0) ||
411  (our_type != AKA_SIM_ID_TYPE_PERMANENT)) {
412  MEM(fr_pair_update_by_da(request->state_ctx, &vp,
413  &request->state, attr_eap_aka_sim_permanent_identity) >= 0);
414  fr_pair_value_bstrndup(vp, in->vp_strvalue, in->vp_length, true);
415 
416  RDEBUG2("%s has incorrect hint byte, expected '%c', got '%c'. "
417  "'hint' byte not stripped",
418  attr_eap_aka_sim_permanent_identity->name,
419  fr_aka_sim_hint_byte(AKA_SIM_ID_TYPE_PERMANENT, expected_method),
420  fr_aka_sim_hint_byte(our_type, our_method));
421  RINDENT();
422  RDEBUG2("&session-state.%pP", vp);
423  REXDENT();
424  } else {
425  /*
426  * To get here the identity must be >= 1 and must have
427  * had the expected hint byte.
428  *
429  * Strip off the hint byte, and then add the permanent
430  * identity to the output list.
431  */
432  MEM(fr_pair_update_by_da(request->state_ctx, &vp,
433  &request->state, attr_eap_aka_sim_permanent_identity) >= 0);
434  fr_pair_value_bstrndup(vp, in->vp_strvalue + 1, in->vp_length - 1, true);
435 
436  RDEBUG2("Stripping 'hint' byte from %s", attr_eap_aka_sim_permanent_identity->name);
437  RINDENT();
438  RDEBUG2("&session-state.%pP", vp);
439  REXDENT();
440  }
441 
442  return 0;
443 }

448 static void identity_to_crypto_identity(request_t *request, eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session,

461 static inline bool after_authentication(eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session)

466 /** Resume after 'store session { ... }'
467  *
468  */
469 static unlang_action_t session_store_resume(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request, void *rctx)
470 {
471  aka_sim_state_enter_t state_enter = (aka_sim_state_enter_t)rctx;
472 
473  switch (request->rcode) {
474  /*
475  * Store failed. Don't send fastauth id
476  */
477  case RLM_MODULE_USER_SECTION_REJECT:
478  pair_delete_reply(attr_eap_aka_sim_next_reauth_id);
479  break;
480 
481  default:
482  break;
483  }
484 
485  pair_delete_request(attr_eap_aka_sim_next_reauth_id);
486 
487  return state_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session_get(request->parent));
488 }

490 /** Resume after 'store pseudonym { ... }'
491  *
492  */
493 static unlang_action_t pseudonym_store_resume(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request, void *rctx)
494 {
495  eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t *inst = talloc_get_type_abort(mctx->instance, eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t);
496  eap_session_t *eap_session = eap_session_get(request->parent);
497  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
498  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
499  aka_sim_state_enter_t state_enter = (aka_sim_state_enter_t)rctx;
500  fr_pair_t *vp;
501  fr_pair_t *new;
502 
503  switch (request->rcode) {
504  /*
505  * Store failed. Don't send pseudonym
506  */
507  case RLM_MODULE_USER_SECTION_REJECT:
508  pair_delete_reply(attr_eap_aka_sim_next_pseudonym);
509  break;
510 
511  default:
512  break;
513  }
514 
515  request->rcode = RLM_MODULE_NOOP; /* Needed because we may call resume functions directly */
516 
517  pair_delete_request(attr_eap_aka_sim_next_pseudonym);
518 
519  vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&request->reply_pairs, attr_eap_aka_sim_next_reauth_id);
520  if (vp) {
521  /*
522  * Generate a random fastauth string
523  */
524  if (vp->vp_length == 0) {
525  char *identity;
526 
527  if (!inst->ephemeral_id_length) {
528  RWDEBUG("Found empty Next-Reauth-Id, and told not to generate one. "
529  "Skipping store session { ... } section");
530 
531  goto done;
532  }
533 
534  MEM(identity = talloc_array(vp, char, inst->ephemeral_id_length + 2));
535  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->type) {
536  case FR_EAP_METHOD_SIM:
537  identity[0] = (char)ID_TAG_SIM_FASTAUTH;
538  break;
539 
540  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA:
541  identity[0] = (char)ID_TAG_AKA_FASTAUTH;
542  break;
543 
544  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME:
545  identity[0] = (char)ID_TAG_AKA_PRIME_FASTAUTH;
546  break;
547 
548  default:
549  break;
550  }
551  fr_rand_str((uint8_t *)identity + 1, inst->ephemeral_id_length, 'a');
552  identity[talloc_array_length(identity) - 1] = '\0';
553 
554  fr_value_box_bstrdup_buffer_shallow(NULL, &vp->data, NULL, identity, false);
555  }
556  pair_update_request(&new, attr_session_id);
557  fr_pair_value_memdup(new, (uint8_t const *)vp->vp_strvalue, vp->vp_length, vp->vp_tainted);
558 
559  MEM(eap_aka_sim_session->fastauth_sent = talloc_bstrndup(eap_aka_sim_session,
560  vp->vp_strvalue, vp->vp_length));
561 
562  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->type) {
563  /*
564  * AKA and SIM use the original MK for session resumption.
565  */
566  case FR_EAP_METHOD_SIM:
567  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA:
568  MEM(pair_update_session_state(&vp, attr_session_data) >= 0);
569  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.mk,
570  sizeof(eap_aka_sim_session->keys.mk), false);
571  break;
572  /*
573  * AKA' KDF 1 generates an additional key k_re
574  * which is used for reauthentication instead
575  * of the MK.
576  */
577  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME:
578  MEM(pair_update_session_state(&vp, attr_session_data) >= 0);
579  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.k_re,
580  sizeof(eap_aka_sim_session->keys.k_re), false);
581  break;
582 
583  default:
584  fr_assert(0);
585  break;
586  }
587 
588  /*
589  * If the counter already exists in session
590  * state increment by 1, otherwise, add the
591  * attribute and set to zero.
592  */
593  vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&request->state, attr_eap_aka_sim_counter);
594  if (vp) {
595  vp->vp_uint16++;
596  /*
597  * Will get incremented by 1 in
598  * reauthentication_send, so when
599  * used, it'll be 1 (as per the standard).
600  */
601  } else {
602  MEM(pair_add_session_state(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_counter) >= 0);
603  vp->vp_uint16 = 0;
604  }
605 
606  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
607  request,
608  inst->actions.store_session,
609  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
610  session_store_resume,
611  mod_signal,
612  rctx);
613  }
614 
615 done:
616  return state_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session_get(request->parent));
617 }
618 
619 /** Implements a set of states for storing pseudonym and fastauth identities
620  *
621  * At the end of challenge or reauthentication rounds, the user may have specified
622  * a pseudonym and fastauth identity to return to the supplicant.
623  *
624  * Call the appropriate sections to persist those values.
625  *
626  * @param[out] p_result Result of calling the module.
627  * @param[in] mctx Module calling ctx.
628  * @param[in] request the current request.
629  * @param[in] eap_session the EAP session
630  * @param[in] state_enter state entry function for the
631  * state to transition to *after* the current
632  * state.
633  */
634 static unlang_action_t session_and_pseudonym_store(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,
635  request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session,
636  aka_sim_state_enter_t state_enter)
637 {
638  eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t *inst = talloc_get_type_abort(mctx->instance, eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t);
639  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
640  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
641  fr_pair_t *vp;
642  fr_pair_t *new;
643 
644  request->rcode = RLM_MODULE_NOOP; /* Needed because we may call resume functions directly */
645 
646  vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&request->reply_pairs, attr_eap_aka_sim_next_pseudonym);
647  if (vp) {
648  /*
649  * Generate a random pseudonym string
650  */
651  if (vp->vp_length == 0) {
652  char *identity;
653 
654  if (!inst->ephemeral_id_length) {
655  RWDEBUG("Found empty Pseudonym-Id, and told not to generate one. "
656  "Skipping store pseudonym { ... } section");
657 
658  return pseudonym_store_resume(p_result, mctx, request, (void *)state_enter);
659  }
660 
661  MEM(identity = talloc_array(vp, char, inst->ephemeral_id_length + 2));
662  fr_rand_str((uint8_t *)identity + 1, inst->ephemeral_id_length, 'a');
663  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->type) {
664  case FR_EAP_METHOD_SIM:
665  identity[0] = (char)ID_TAG_SIM_PSEUDONYM;
666  break;
667 
668  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA:
669  identity[0] = (char)ID_TAG_AKA_PSEUDONYM;
670  break;
671 
672  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME:
673  identity[0] = (char)ID_TAG_AKA_PRIME_PSEUDONYM;
674  break;
675 
676  default:
677  break;
678  }
679  identity[talloc_array_length(identity) - 1] = '\0';
680  fr_value_box_bstrdup_buffer_shallow(NULL, &vp->data, NULL, identity, false);
681  }
682  pair_update_request(&new, attr_eap_aka_sim_next_pseudonym);
683  fr_pair_value_copy(new, vp);
684 
685  MEM(eap_aka_sim_session->pseudonym_sent = talloc_bstrndup(eap_aka_sim_session,
686  vp->vp_strvalue, vp->vp_length));
687 
688  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
689  request,
690  inst->actions.store_pseudonym,
691  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
692  pseudonym_store_resume,
693  mod_signal,
694  (void *)state_enter);
695  }
696 
697  return pseudonym_store_resume(p_result, mctx, request, (void *)state_enter);
698 }

795 /** Encode EAP-SIM/AKA['] attributes
796  *
797  */
798 static int common_encode(request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session, uint16_t subtype,
799  uint8_t const *hmac_extra, size_t hmac_extra_len)
800 {
801  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
802  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
803  fr_cursor_t cursor;
804  fr_cursor_t to_encode;
805  fr_pair_t *head = NULL, *vp, *subtype_vp;
806  ssize_t ret;
807  fr_aka_sim_encode_ctx_t encoder_ctx = {
808  .root = fr_dict_root(dict_eap_aka_sim),
809  .keys = &eap_aka_sim_session->keys,
810 
811  .iv = { 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
812  0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00 },
813  .iv_included = false,
814 
815  .hmac_md = eap_aka_sim_session->mac_md,
816  .eap_packet = eap_session->this_round->request,
817  .hmac_extra = hmac_extra,
818  .hmac_extra_len = hmac_extra_len
819  };
820 
821  /*
822  * Set the subtype to identity request
823  */
824  MEM(pair_update_reply(&subtype_vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_subtype) >= 0);
825  subtype_vp->vp_uint16 = subtype;
826 
827  /*
828  * State what kind of request we're sending
829  */
830  if (RDEBUG_ENABLED2) {
831  switch (subtype) {
832  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_SIM_START:
833  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_IDENTITY:
834  RDEBUG2("Sending EAP-Request/%pV (%s)", &subtype_vp->data,
835  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_aka_sim_id_request_table, eap_aka_sim_session->id_req, "<INVALID>"));
836  break;
837 
838  default:
839  RDEBUG2("Sending EAP-Request/%pV", &subtype_vp->data);
840  break;
841  }
842  }
843 
844  fr_cursor_init(&cursor, &request->reply_pairs);
845  fr_cursor_init(&to_encode, &head);
846 
847  /*
848  * We have to be *SUPER* careful here not to reorder
849  * attributes, because for EAP-SIM the RAND values
850  * must be inserted into the packet in exactly the
851  * same order as they appear in fr_sim_keys_t
852  * otherwise the KDF will produce a different
853  * result.
854  */
855  while ((vp = fr_cursor_current(&cursor))) {
856  if (!fr_dict_attr_common_parent(encoder_ctx.root, vp->da, true)) {
857  fr_cursor_next(&cursor);
858  continue;
859  }
860  vp = fr_cursor_remove(&cursor);
861 
862  /*
863  * Silently discard encrypted attributes until
864  * the peer should have k_encr. These can be
865  * added by policy, and seem to cause
866  * wpa_supplicant to fail if sent before the challenge.
867  */
868  if (!eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted &&
869  fr_dict_attr_common_parent(attr_eap_aka_sim_encr_data, vp->da, true)) {
870  RWDEBUG("Silently discarding &reply.%s: Encrypted attributes not allowed in this round",
871  vp->da->name);
872  talloc_free(vp);
873  continue;
874  }
875 
876  fr_cursor_prepend(&to_encode, vp);
877  }
878 
879 
880  RDEBUG2("Encoding attributes");
881  log_request_pair_list(L_DBG_LVL_2, request, head, NULL);
882 
883  eap_session->this_round->request->type.num = eap_aka_sim_session->type;
884  eap_session->this_round->request->id = eap_aka_sim_session->id++ & 0xff;
885  eap_session->this_round->set_request_id = true;
886 
887  ret = fr_aka_sim_encode(request, head, &encoder_ctx);
888  fr_cursor_head(&to_encode);
889  fr_cursor_free_list(&to_encode);
890 
891  if (ret < 0) {
892  RPEDEBUG("Failed encoding attributes");
893  return -1;
894  }
895  return 0;
896 }

901 static unlang_action_t common_eap_failure_send(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)

911 /** Send a EAP-Request/(AKA|SIM)-Notification (Failure) message to the supplicant
912  *
913  */
914 static unlang_action_t common_failure_notification_send(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,
915  request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)
916 {
917  fr_pair_t *vp, *notification_vp;
918  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
919  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
920 
921  /*
922  * Allow the user to specify specific failure notification
923  * types. We assume the user knows what they're doing and
924  * only toggle success and phase bits.
925  *
926  * This allows custom notification schemes to be implemented.
927  *
928  * If this is prior to authentication, valid values are:
929  * - FR_NOTIFICATION_VALUE_GENERAL_FAILURE
930  *
931  * If this is after authentication, valid values are:
932  * - FR_NOTIFICATION_VALUE_GENERAL_FAILURE_AFTER_AUTHENTICATION
933  * - FR_NOTIFICATION_VALUE_TEMPORARILY_DENIED - User has been
934  * temporarily denied access to the requested service.
935  * - FR_NOTIFICATION_VALUE_NOT_SUBSCRIBED
936  * User has not subscribed to the requested service.
937  */
938  notification_vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&request->reply_pairs, attr_eap_aka_sim_notification);
939 
940  /*
941  * Change the failure notification depending where
942  * we are in the eap_aka_state machine.
943  */
944  if (after_authentication(eap_aka_sim_session)) {
945  if (!notification_vp) {
946  MEM(pair_add_reply(&notification_vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_notification) >= 0);
947  notification_vp->vp_uint16 = eap_aka_sim_session->failure_type; /* Default will be zero */
948  }
949 
950  notification_vp->vp_uint16 &= ~0x4000; /* Unset phase bit */
951 
952  /*
953  * Include the counter attribute if we're failing
954  * after a reauthentication success.
955  *
956  * RFC 4187 Section #9.10
957  *
958  * If EAP-Request/AKA-Notification is used on
959  * a fast re-authentication exchange, and if
960  * the P bit in AT_NOTIFICATION is set to zero,
961  * then AT_COUNTER is used for replay protection.
962  * In this case, the AT_ENCR_DATA and AT_IV
963  * attributes MUST be included, and the
964  * encapsulated plaintext attributes MUST include
965  * the AT_COUNTER attribute. The counter value
966  * included in AT_COUNTER MUST be the same
967  * as in the EAP-Request/AKA-Reauthentication
968  * packet on the same fast re-authentication
969  * exchange.
970  *
971  * If the counter is used it should never be zero,
972  * as it's incremented on first reauthentication
973  * request.
974  */
975  if (eap_aka_sim_session->reauthentication_success) {
976  MEM(pair_update_reply(&notification_vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_counter) >= 0);
977  notification_vp->vp_uint16 = eap_aka_sim_session->keys.reauth.counter;
978  }
979 
980  /*
981  * If we're after the challenge phase
982  * then we need to include a MAC to
983  * protect notifications.
984  */
985  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_mac) >= 0);
986  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, NULL, 0, false);
987  } else {
988  /*
989  * Only valid code is general failure
990  */
991  if (!notification_vp) {
992  MEM(pair_add_reply(&notification_vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_notification) >= 0);
993  notification_vp->vp_uint16 = FR_NOTIFICATION_VALUE_GENERAL_FAILURE;
994  /*
995  * User supplied failure code
996  */
997  } else {
998  notification_vp->vp_uint16 |= 0x4000; /* Set phase bit */
999  }
1000  }
1001  notification_vp->vp_uint16 &= ~0x8000; /* In both cases success bit should be low */
1002 
1003  eap_session->this_round->request->code = FR_EAP_CODE_REQUEST;
1004 
1005  /*
1006  * Encode the packet
1007  */
1008  if (common_encode(request, eap_session, FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_SIM_NOTIFICATION, NULL, 0) < 0) {
1009  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
1010  }
1011 
1012  RETURN_MODULE_HANDLED;
1013 }
1014 
1015 /** Add MPPE keys to the request being sent to the supplicant
1016  *
1017  * The only work to be done is the add the appropriate SEND/RECV
1018  * attributes derived from the MSK.
1019  */
1020 static unlang_action_t common_eap_success_send(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)
1021 {
1022  uint8_t *p;
1023  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session;
1024 
1025  RDEBUG2("Sending EAP-Success");
1026 
1027  eap_session->this_round->request->code = FR_EAP_CODE_SUCCESS;
1028  eap_session->finished = true;
1029 
1030  eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque, eap_aka_sim_session_t);
1031 
1032  RDEBUG2("Adding attributes for MSK");
1033  p = eap_aka_sim_session->keys.msk;
1034  eap_add_reply(request->parent, attr_ms_mppe_recv_key, p, EAP_TLS_MPPE_KEY_LEN);
1035  p += EAP_TLS_MPPE_KEY_LEN;
1036  eap_add_reply(request->parent, attr_ms_mppe_send_key, p, EAP_TLS_MPPE_KEY_LEN);
1037 
1038  RETURN_MODULE_OK;

1041 /** Send a EAP-Request/(AKA|SIM)-Notification (Success) message to the supplicant
1042  *
1043  */
1044 static unlang_action_t common_success_notification_send(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,
1045  request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)
1046 {
1047  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque, eap_aka_sim_session_t);
1048  fr_pair_t *vp;
1049 
1050  eap_session->this_round->request->code = FR_EAP_CODE_REQUEST;
1051 
1052  if (!fr_cond_assert(after_authentication(eap_aka_sim_session))) {
1053  RETURN_MODULE_FAIL;
1054  }
1055 
1056  /*
1057  * If we're in this state success bit is
1058  * high phase bit is low.
1059  */
1060  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_notification) >= 0);
1061  vp->vp_uint16 = FR_NOTIFICATION_VALUE_SUCCESS;
1062 
1063  /*
1064  * RFC 4187 section #9.10
1065  *
1066  * If EAP-Request/AKA-Notification is used on
1067  * a fast re-authentication exchange, and if
1068  * the P bit in AT_NOTIFICATION is set to zero,
1069  * then AT_COUNTER is used for replay protection.
1070  * In this case, the AT_ENCR_DATA and AT_IV
1071  * attributes MUST be included, and the
1072  * encapsulated plaintext attributes MUST include
1073  * the AT_COUNTER attribute. The counter value
1074  * included in AT_COUNTER MUST be the same
1075  * as in the EAP-Request/AKA-Reauthentication
1076  * packet on the same fast re-authentication
1077  * exchange.
1078  *
1079  * If the counter is used it should never be zero,
1080  * as it's incremented on first reauthentication
1081  * request.
1082  */
1083  if (eap_aka_sim_session->keys.reauth.counter > 0) {
1084  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_counter) >= 0);
1085  vp->vp_uint16 = eap_aka_sim_session->keys.reauth.counter;
1086  }
1087 
1088  /*
1089  * Need to include an AT_MAC attribute so that
1090  * it will get calculated.
1091  */
1092  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_mac) >= 0);
1093  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, NULL, 0, false);
1094 
1095  /*
1096  * Encode the packet
1097  */
1098  if (common_encode(request, eap_session, FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_SIM_NOTIFICATION, NULL, 0) < 0) {
1099  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
1100  }
1101 
1102  RETURN_MODULE_HANDLED;
1103 }

1122 /** Send a EAP-Request/(AKA|SIM)-Reauthenticate message to the supplicant
1123  *
1124  */
1125 static unlang_action_t common_reauthentication_request_compose(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request,
1126  eap_session_t *eap_session)
1127 {
1128  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
1129  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
1130  fr_pair_t *to_peer = request->reply_pairs, *vp;
1131 
1132  fr_pair_t *kdf_id;
1133 
1134  /*
1135  * Allow override of KDF Identity
1136  *
1137  * Because certain handset manufacturers don't
1138  * implement RFC 4187 correctly and use the
1139  * wrong identity as input the the PRF/KDF.
1140  *
1141  * Not seen any doing this for re-authentication
1142  * but you never know...
1143  */
1144  kdf_id = fr_pair_find_by_da(&request->control_pairs, attr_eap_aka_sim_kdf_identity);
1145  if (kdf_id) {
1146  identity_to_crypto_identity(request, eap_aka_sim_session,
1147  (uint8_t const *)kdf_id->vp_strvalue, kdf_id->vp_length);
1148  fr_pair_delete_by_da(&request->control_pairs, attr_eap_aka_sim_kdf_identity);
1149  }
1150 
1151  RDEBUG2("Generating new session keys");
1152 
1153  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->type) {
1154  /*
1155  * The GSM and UMTS KDF_0 mutate their keys using
1156  * and identical algorithm.
1157  */
1158  case FR_EAP_METHOD_SIM:
1159  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA:
1160  if (fr_aka_sim_vector_gsm_umts_kdf_0_reauth_from_attrs(request, request->state,
1161  &eap_aka_sim_session->keys) != 0) {
1162  request_new_id:
1163  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->last_id_req) {
1164  /*
1165  * Got here processing EAP-Identity-Response
1166  * If this is the *true* reauth ID, then
1167  * there's no point in setting AKA_SIM_ANY_ID_REQ.
1168  */
1169  case AKA_SIM_NO_ID_REQ:
1170  case AKA_SIM_ANY_ID_REQ:
1171  RDEBUG2("Composing EAP-Request/Reauthentication failed. Clearing reply attributes and "
1172  "requesting additional Identity");
1173  fr_pair_list_free(&request->reply_pairs);
1174  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_FULLAUTH_ID_REQ;
1175  return common_identity_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
1176 
1177  case AKA_SIM_FULLAUTH_ID_REQ:
1178  case AKA_SIM_PERMANENT_ID_REQ:
1179  REDEBUG("Last requested fullauth or permanent ID, "
1180  "but received, or were told we received (by policy), "
1181  "a fastauth ID. Cannot continue");
1182  failure:
1183  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
1184  }
1185  }
1186  if (fr_aka_sim_crypto_kdf_0_reauth(&eap_aka_sim_session->keys) < 0) goto request_new_id;
1187  break;
1188 
1189  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME:
1190  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->kdf) {
1191  case FR_KDF_VALUE_PRIME_WITH_CK_PRIME_IK_PRIME:
1192  if (fr_aka_sim_vector_umts_kdf_1_reauth_from_attrs(request, request->state,
1193  &eap_aka_sim_session->keys) != 0) {
1194  goto request_new_id;
1195  }
1196  if (fr_aka_sim_crypto_umts_kdf_1_reauth(&eap_aka_sim_session->keys) < 0) goto request_new_id;
1197  break;
1198 
1199  default:
1200  fr_assert(0);
1201  break;
1202  }
1203  break;
1204 
1205  default:
1206  fr_assert(0);
1207  break;
1208  }
1209 
1210  if (RDEBUG_ENABLED3) fr_aka_sim_crypto_keys_log(request, &eap_aka_sim_session->keys);
1211 
1212  /*
1213  * Add AT_IV, AT_COUNTER, AT_NONCE_S, and AT_MAC to to reply
1214  * The user may have added AT_NEXT_REAUTH_ID, in which case
1215  * we'll have sent that too.
1216  */
1217  eap_session->this_round->request->code = FR_EAP_CODE_REQUEST;
1218 
1219  /*
1220  * Indicate we'd like to use protected success messages
1221  * with AT_RESULT_IND
1222  *
1223  * Use our default, but allow user override too.
1224  */
1225  vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&to_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_result_ind);
1226  if (vp) eap_aka_sim_session->send_result_ind = vp->vp_bool;
1227 
1228  /*
1229  * RFC 5448 says AT_BIDDING is only sent in the challenge
1230  * not in reauthentication, so don't add that here.
1231  */
1232 
1233  /*
1234  * Add AT_NONCE_S
1235  */
1236  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_nonce_s) >= 0);
1237  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.reauth.nonce_s,
1238  sizeof(eap_aka_sim_session->keys.reauth.nonce_s), false);
1239 
1240  /*
1241  * Add AT_COUNTER
1242  */
1243  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_counter) >= 0);
1244  vp->vp_uint16 = eap_aka_sim_session->keys.reauth.counter;
1245 
1246  /*
1247  * need to include an empty AT_MAC attribute so that
1248  * the mac will get calculated.
1249  */
1250  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_mac) >= 0);
1251  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, NULL, 0, false);
1252 
1253  /*
1254  * If there's no checkcode_md we're not doing
1255  * checkcodes.
1256  */
1257  if (eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_md) {
1258  /*
1259  * If we have checkcode data, send that to the peer
1260  * in AT_CHECKCODE for validation.
1261  */
1262  if (eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_state) {
1263  ssize_t slen;
1264 
1265  slen = fr_aka_sim_crypto_finalise_checkcode(eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode,
1266  &eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_state);
1267  if (slen < 0) {
1268  RPEDEBUG("Failed calculating checkcode");
1269  goto failure;
1270  }
1271  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len = slen;
1272 
1273  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_checkcode) >= 0);
1274  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode, slen, false);
1275  /*
1276  * If we don't have checkcode data, then we exchanged
1277  * no identity packets, so checkcode is zero.
1278  */
1279  } else {
1280  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_checkcode) >= 0);
1281  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, NULL, 0, false);
1282  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len = 0;
1283  }
1284  }
1285 
1286  /*
1287  * We've sent the challenge so the peer should now be able
1288  * to accept encrypted attributes.
1289  */
1290  eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted = true;
1291 
1292  return session_and_pseudonym_store(p_result, mctx,request, eap_session, common_reauthentication_request_send);
1293 }

1316  request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)
1317 {
1318  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque, eap_aka_sim_session_t);
1319  fr_pair_t *to_peer = request->reply_pairs, *vp;
1320  fr_aka_sim_vector_src_t src = AKA_SIM_VECTOR_SRC_AUTO;
1321 
1322  fr_pair_t *kdf_id;
1323 
1324  /*
1325  * Allow override of KDF Identity
1326  *
1327  * Because certain handset manufacturers don't
1328  * implement RFC 4187 correctly and use the
1329  * wrong identity as input the the PRF/KDF.
1330  */
1331  kdf_id = fr_pair_find_by_da(&request->control_pairs, attr_eap_aka_sim_kdf_identity);
1332  if (kdf_id) {
1333  identity_to_crypto_identity(request, eap_aka_sim_session,
1334  (uint8_t const *)kdf_id->vp_strvalue, kdf_id->vp_length);
1335  fr_pair_delete_by_da(&request->control_pairs, attr_eap_aka_sim_kdf_identity);
1336  }
1337 
1338  RDEBUG2("Acquiring UMTS vector(s)");
1339 
1340  if (eap_aka_sim_session->type == FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME) {
1341  /*
1342  * Copy the network name the user specified for
1343  * key derivation purposes.
1344  */
1345  vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&to_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_kdf_input);
1346  if (vp) {
1347  talloc_free(eap_aka_sim_session->keys.network);
1348  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.network = talloc_memdup(eap_aka_sim_session,
1349  (uint8_t const *)vp->vp_strvalue,
1350  vp->vp_length);
1351  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.network_len = vp->vp_length;
1352  } else {
1353  REDEBUG("No network name available, can't set AT_KDF_INPUT");
1354  failure:
1355  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
1356  }
1357 
1358  /*
1359  * We don't allow the user to specify
1360  * the KDF currently.
1361  */
1362  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_kdf) >= 0);
1363  vp->vp_uint16 = eap_aka_sim_session->kdf;
1364  }
1365 
1366  /*
1367  * Get vectors from attribute or generate
1368  * them using COMP128-* or Milenage.
1369  */
1370  if (fr_aka_sim_vector_umts_from_attrs(request, request->control_pairs, &eap_aka_sim_session->keys, &src) != 0) {
1371  REDEBUG("Failed retrieving UMTS vectors");
1372  goto failure;
1373  }
1374 
1375  /*
1376  * Don't leave the AMF hanging around
1377  */
1378  if (eap_aka_sim_session->type == FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME) pair_delete_control(attr_sim_amf);
1379 
1380  /*
1381  * All set, calculate keys!
1382  */
1383  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->type) {
1384  default:
1385  case FR_EAP_METHOD_SIM:
1386  fr_assert(0); /* EAP-SIM has its own Challenge state */
1387  break;
1388 
1389  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA:
1390  fr_aka_sim_crypto_umts_kdf_0(&eap_aka_sim_session->keys);
1391  break;
1392 
1393  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME:
1394  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->kdf) {
1395  case FR_KDF_VALUE_PRIME_WITH_CK_PRIME_IK_PRIME:
1396  fr_aka_sim_crypto_umts_kdf_1(&eap_aka_sim_session->keys);
1397  break;
1398 
1399  default:
1400  fr_assert(0);
1401  break;
1402  }
1403  }
1404  if (RDEBUG_ENABLED3) fr_aka_sim_crypto_keys_log(request, &eap_aka_sim_session->keys);
1405 
1406  eap_session->this_round->request->code = FR_EAP_CODE_REQUEST;
1407 
1408  /*
1409  * Indicate we'd like to use protected success messages
1410  * with AT_RESULT_IND
1411  *
1412  * Use our default, but allow user override too.
1413  */
1414  vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&to_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_result_ind);
1415  if (vp) eap_aka_sim_session->send_result_ind = vp->vp_bool;
1416 
1417  /*
1418  * See if we're indicating we want EAP-AKA'
1419  * If so include AT_BIDDING with the correct
1420  * value.
1421  */
1422  vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&to_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_bidding);
1423  if (vp) {
1424  eap_aka_sim_session->send_at_bidding_prefer_prime =
1425  (vp->vp_uint16 == FR_BIDDING_VALUE_PREFER_AKA_PRIME);
1426  }
1427 
1428  /*
1429  * These attributes are only allowed with
1430  * EAP-AKA', protect users from themselves.
1431  */
1432  if (eap_aka_sim_session->type == FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA) {
1433  pair_delete_reply(attr_eap_aka_sim_kdf_input);
1434  pair_delete_reply(attr_eap_aka_sim_kdf);
1435  }
1436 
1437  /*
1438  * Okay, we got the challenge! Put it into an attribute.
1439  */
1440  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_rand) >= 0);
1441  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.umts.vector.rand, AKA_SIM_VECTOR_UMTS_RAND_SIZE, false);
1442 
1443  /*
1444  * Send the AUTN value to the client, so it can authenticate
1445  * whoever has knowledge of the Ki.
1446  */
1447  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_autn) >= 0);
1448  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.umts.vector.autn, AKA_SIM_VECTOR_UMTS_AUTN_SIZE, false);
1449 
1450  /*
1451  * need to include an AT_MAC attribute so that it will get
1452  * calculated.
1453  */
1454  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_mac) >= 0);
1455  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, NULL, 0, false);
1456 
1457  /*
1458  * If we have checkcode data, send that to the peer
1459  * in AT_CHECKCODE for validation.
1460  */
1461  if (eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_state) {
1462  ssize_t slen;
1463 
1464  slen = fr_aka_sim_crypto_finalise_checkcode(eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode,
1465  &eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_state);
1466  if (slen < 0) {
1467  RPEDEBUG("Failed calculating checkcode");
1468  goto failure;
1469  }
1470  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len = slen;
1471 
1472  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_checkcode) >= 0);
1473  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode, slen, false);
1474  /*
1475  * If we don't have checkcode data, then we exchanged
1476  * no identity packets, so AT_CHECKCODE is zero.
1477  */
1478  } else {
1479  MEM(pair_update_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_checkcode) >= 0);
1480  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, NULL, 0, false);
1481  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len = 0;
1482  }
1483 
1484  /*
1485  * We've sent the challenge so the peer should now be able
1486  * to accept encrypted attributes.
1487  */
1488  eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted = true;
1489 
1490  return session_and_pseudonym_store(p_result, mctx,request, eap_session, aka_challenge_request_send);
1491 }

1595 /** Send a EAP-Request/AKA-Identity message to the supplicant
1596  *
1597  * There are three types of user identities that can be implemented
1598  * - Permanent identities such as 0123456789098765@myoperator.com
1599  * Permanent identities can be identified by the leading zero followed by
1600  * by 15 digits (the IMSI number).
1601  * - Ephemeral identities (pseudonyms). These are identities assigned for
1602  * identity privacy so the user can't be tracked. These can identities
1603  * can either be generated as per the 3GPP 'Security aspects of non-3GPP accesses'
1604  * document section 14, where a set of up to 16 encryption keys are used
1605  * to reversibly encrypt the IMSI. Alternatively the pseudonym can be completely
1606  * randomised and stored in a datastore.
1607  * - A fast resumption ID which resolves to data used for fast resumption.
1608  *
1609  * In order to perform full authentication the original IMSI is required for
1610  * forwarding to the HLR. In the case where we can't match/decrypt the pseudonym,
1611  * or can't perform fast resumption, we need to request the full identity from
1612  * the supplicant.
1613  *
1614  * @param[out] p_result Result of calling the module, one of:
1615  * - RLM_MODULE_HANDLED on success.
1616  * - anything else on failure.
1617  * @param[in] mctx module calling ctx.
1618  * @param[in] request The current subrequest.
1619  * @param[in] eap_session to continue.
1620  */
1621 static unlang_action_t aka_identity_request_send(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,
1622  request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)
1623 {
1624  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
1625  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
1626  eap_session->this_round->request->code = FR_EAP_CODE_REQUEST;
1627 
1628  /*
1629  * Update eap_aka_sim_session->id_req in case the the
1630  * user set attributes in `send Identity-Request { ... }`
1631  * Also removes all existing id_req attributes
1632  * from the reply.
1633  */
1634  identity_req_set_by_user(request, eap_aka_sim_session);
1635 
1636  /*
1637  * Select the right type of identity request attribute
1638  *
1639  * Implement checks on identity request order described
1640  * by RFC4187 section #4.1.5.
1641  *
1642  * The internal state machine should always handle this
1643  * correctly, but the user may have other ideas...
1644  */
1645  if (identity_req_pairs_add(request, eap_aka_sim_session) < 0) {
1646  failure:
1647  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
1648  }
1649  eap_aka_sim_session->last_id_req = eap_aka_sim_session->id_req; /* Record what we last requested */
1650 
1651  /*
1652  * Encode the packet
1653  */
1654  if (common_encode(request, eap_session, FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_IDENTITY, NULL, 0) < 0) goto failure;
1655 
1656  /*
1657  * Digest the packet contents, updating our checkcode.
1658  */
1659  if (eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_md) {
1660  if (!eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_state &&
1661  fr_aka_sim_crypto_init_checkcode(eap_aka_sim_session, &eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_state,
1662  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_md) < 0) {
1663  RPEDEBUG("Failed initialising checkcode");
1664  goto failure;
1665  }
1666  if (fr_aka_sim_crypto_update_checkcode(eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_state,
1667  eap_session->this_round->request) < 0) {
1668  RPEDEBUG("Failed updating checkcode");
1669  goto failure;
1670  }
1671  }
1672 
1673  RETURN_MODULE_HANDLED;
1674 }
1675 
1676 /** Send a EAP-Request/SIM-Start message to the supplicant
1677  *
1678  * There are three types of user identities that can be implemented
1679  * - Permanent identities such as 0123456789098765@myoperator.com
1680  * Permanent identities can be identified by the leading zero followed by
1681  * by 15 digits (the IMSI number).
1682  * - Ephemeral identities (pseudonyms). These are identities assigned for
1683  * identity privacy so the user can't be tracked. These can identities
1684  * can either be generated as per the 3GPP 'Security aspects of non-3GPP accesses'
1685  * document section 14, where a set of up to 16 encryption keys are used
1686  * to reversibly encrypt the IMSI. Alternatively the pseudonym can be completely
1687  * randomised and stored in a datastore.
1688  * - A fast resumption ID which resolves to data used for fast resumption.
1689  *
1690  * In order to perform full authentication the original IMSI is required for
1691  * forwarding to the HLR. In the case where we can't match/decrypt the pseudonym,
1692  * or can't perform fast resumption, we need to request the full identity from
1693  * the supplicant.
1694  *
1695  * @param[out] p_result Result of calling the module, one of:
1696  * - RLM_MODULE_HANDLED on success.
1697  * - anything else on failure.
1698  * @param[in] mctx module calling context.
1699  * @param[in] request The current subrequest.
1700  * @param[in] eap_session to continue.
1701  */
1702 static unlang_action_t sim_start_request_send(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,
1703  request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)
1704 {
1705  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
1706  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
1707  fr_pair_t *vp;
1708  fr_cursor_t cursor;
1709  uint8_t *p, *end;
1710 
1711  eap_session->this_round->request->code = FR_EAP_CODE_REQUEST;
1712 
1713  p = eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.version_list;
1714  end = p + sizeof(eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.version_list);
1715  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.version_list_len = 0;
1716 
1717  /*
1718  * If the user provided no versions, then
1719  * just add the default (1).
1720  */
1721  if (!(fr_pair_find_by_da(&request->reply_pairs, attr_eap_aka_sim_version_list))) {
1722  MEM(pair_add_reply(&vp, attr_eap_aka_sim_version_list) >= 0);
1723  vp->vp_uint16 = EAP_SIM_VERSION;
1724  }
1725 
1726  /*
1727  * Iterate over the the versions adding them
1728  * to the version list we use for keying.
1729  */
1730  for (vp = fr_cursor_init(&cursor, &request->reply_pairs); vp; vp = fr_cursor_next(&cursor)) {
1731  if (vp->da != attr_eap_aka_sim_version_list) continue;
1732 
1733  if ((end - p) < 2) break;
1734 
1735  /*
1736  * Store as big endian
1737  */
1738  *p++ = (vp->vp_uint16 & 0xff00) >> 8;
1739  *p++ = (vp->vp_uint16 & 0x00ff);
1740  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.version_list_len += sizeof(uint16_t);
1741  }
1742 
1743  /*
1744  * Update eap_aka_sim_session->id_req in case the the
1745  * user set attributes in `send Identity-Request { ... }`
1746  * Also removes all existing id_req attributes
1747  * from the reply.
1748  */
1749  identity_req_set_by_user(request, eap_aka_sim_session);
1750 
1751  /*
1752  * Select the right type of identity request attribute
1753  *
1754  * Implement checks on identity request order described
1755  * by RFC4186 section #4.2.5.
1756  *
1757  * The internal state machine should always handle this
1758  * correctly, but the user may have other ideas...
1759  */
1760  if (identity_req_pairs_add(request, eap_aka_sim_session) < 0) {
1761  failure:
1762  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
1763  }
1764  eap_aka_sim_session->last_id_req = eap_aka_sim_session->id_req; /* Record what we last requested */
1765 
1766  /*
1767  * Encode the packet
1768  */
1769  if (common_encode(request, eap_session, FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_SIM_START, NULL, 0) < 0) goto failure;
1770 
1771  RETURN_MODULE_HANDLED;
1772 }

1774 /** Print debugging information, and write new state to eap_session->process
1775  *
1776  */
1777 static inline void state_transition(request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session,
1778  module_method_t new_state)
1779 {
1780  module_method_t old_state = eap_session->process;
1781 
1782  if (new_state != old_state) {
1783  RDEBUG2("Changed state %s -> %s",
1784  module_state_method_to_str(aka_sim_stable_table, old_state, "<unknown>"),
1785  module_state_method_to_str(aka_sim_stable_table, new_state, "<unknown>"));
1786  } else {
1787  RDEBUG2("Reentering state %s",
1788  module_state_method_to_str(aka_sim_stable_table, old_state, "<unknown>"));
1789  }
1790 
1791  eap_session->process = new_state;
1792 }

2207 static unlang_action_t common_reauthentication_enter(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,

2504 /** Process a EAP-Response/(AKA|SIM)-Reauthentication message - The response to our EAP-Request/(AKA|SIM)-Reauthentication message
2505  *
2506  */
2507 static unlang_action_t common_reauthentication_response_process(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request,
2508  eap_session_t *eap_session)
2509 {
2510  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
2511  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
2512 
2513  uint8_t calc_mac[AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE];
2514  ssize_t slen;
2515  fr_pair_t *mac, *checkcode;
2516  fr_pair_t *from_peer = request->request_pairs;
2517 
2518  mac = fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_mac);
2519  if (!mac) {
2520  REDEBUG("Missing AT_MAC attribute");
2521  failure:
2522  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2523  }
2524  if (mac->vp_length != AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE) {
2525  REDEBUG("MAC has incorrect length, expected %u bytes got %zu bytes",
2526  AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE, mac->vp_length);
2527  goto failure;
2528  }
2529 
2530  slen = fr_aka_sim_crypto_sign_packet(calc_mac, eap_session->this_round->response, true,
2531  eap_aka_sim_session->mac_md,
2532  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.k_aut, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.k_aut_len,
2533  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.reauth.nonce_s,
2534  sizeof(eap_aka_sim_session->keys.reauth.nonce_s));
2535  if (slen < 0) {
2536  RPEDEBUG("Failed calculating MAC");
2537  goto failure;
2538  } else if (slen == 0) {
2539  REDEBUG("Zero length AT_MAC attribute");
2540  goto failure;
2541  }
2542 
2543  if (memcmp(mac->vp_octets, calc_mac, sizeof(calc_mac)) == 0) {
2544  RDEBUG2("Received MAC matches calculated MAC");
2545  } else {
2546  REDEBUG("Received MAC does not match calculated MAC");
2547  RHEXDUMP_INLINE2(mac->vp_octets, AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE, "Received");
2548  RHEXDUMP_INLINE2(calc_mac, AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE, "Expected");
2549  goto failure;
2550  }
2551 
2552  /*
2553  * If the peer doesn't include a checkcode then that
2554  * means they don't support it, and we can't validate
2555  * their view of the identity packets.
2556  */
2557  checkcode = fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_checkcode);
2558  if (checkcode) {
2559  if (checkcode->vp_length != eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len) {
2560  REDEBUG("Received checkcode's length (%zu) does not match calculated checkcode's length (%zu)",
2561  checkcode->vp_length, eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len);
2562  goto failure;
2563  }
2564 
2565  if (memcmp(checkcode->vp_octets, eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode,
2566  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len) == 0) {
2567  RDEBUG2("Received checkcode matches calculated checkcode");
2568  } else {
2569  REDEBUG("Received checkcode does not match calculated checkcode");
2570  RHEXDUMP_INLINE2(checkcode->vp_octets, checkcode->vp_length, "Received");
2571  RHEXDUMP_INLINE2(eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode,
2572  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len, "Expected");
2573  goto failure;
2574  }
2575  /*
2576  * Only print something if we calculated a checkcode
2577  */
2578  } else if (eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len > 0){
2579  RDEBUG2("Peer didn't include AT_CHECKCODE, skipping checkcode validation");
2580  }
2581 
2582  /*
2583  * Check to see if the supplicant sent
2584  * AT_COUNTER_TOO_SMALL, if they did then we
2585  * clear out reauth information and enter the
2586  * challenge state.
2587  */
2588  if (fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_counter_too_small)) {
2589  RWDEBUG("Peer sent AT_COUNTER_TOO_SMALL (indicating our AT_COUNTER value (%u) wasn't fresh)",
2590  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.reauth.counter);
2591 
2592  fr_aka_sim_vector_umts_reauth_clear(&eap_aka_sim_session->keys);
2593  eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted = false;
2594 
2595  return aka_challenge_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2596  }
2597 
2598  /*
2599  * If the peer wants a Success notification, and
2600  * we included AT_RESULT_IND then send a success
2601  * notification, otherwise send a normal EAP-Success.
2602  *
2603  * RFC 4187 Section #6.2. Result Indications
2604  */
2605  if (eap_aka_sim_session->send_result_ind) {
2606  if (!fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_result_ind)) {
2607  RDEBUG("We wanted to use protected result indications, but peer does not");
2608  eap_aka_sim_session->send_result_ind = false;
2609  } else {
2610  return common_success_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2611  }
2612  } else if (fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_result_ind)) {
2613  RDEBUG("Peer wanted to use protected result indications, but we do not");
2614  }
2615 
2616  eap_aka_sim_session->reauthentication_success = true;
2617 
2618  return common_eap_success_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2619 }
2620 
2621 /** Process a EAP-Response/AKA-Challenge message - The response to our EAP-Request/AKA-Challenge message

2654  goto failure;
2655  } else if (slen == 0) {
2656  REDEBUG("Zero length AT_MAC attribute");

2670  * If the peer doesn't include a checkcode then that

2686  RDEBUG2("Received checkcode matches calculated checkcode");

2690  RHEXDUMP_INLINE2(eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode,
2691  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len, "Expected");
2692  goto failure;
2693  }
2694  /*
2695  * Only print something if we calculated a checkcode
2696  */
2697  } else if (eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_len > 0){
2698  RDEBUG2("Peer didn't include AT_CHECKCODE, skipping checkcode validation");
2699  }

2710  vp->vp_length, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.umts.vector.xres_len);
2711  goto failure;
2712  }

2717  RHEXDUMP_INLINE2(eap_aka_sim_session->keys.umts.vector.xres,
2718  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.umts.vector.xres_len, "XRES :");
2719  goto failure;
2720  }
2721 
2722  RDEBUG2("Received RES matches calculated XRES");
2723 
2724  eap_aka_sim_session->challenge_success = true;
2725 
2726  /*
2727  * If the peer wants a Success notification, and
2728  * we included AT_RESULT_IND then send a success
2729  * notification, otherwise send a normal EAP-Success.
2730  *
2731  * RFC 4187 Section #6.2. Result Indications
2732  */
2733  if (eap_aka_sim_session->send_result_ind) {
2734  if (!fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_result_ind)) {
2735  RDEBUG("We wanted to use protected result indications, but peer does not");
2736  eap_aka_sim_session->send_result_ind = false;
2737  } else {
2738  return common_success_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2739  }
2740  } else if (fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_result_ind)) {
2741  RDEBUG("Peer wanted to use protected result indications, but we do not");
2742  }
2743 
2744  return common_eap_success_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2745 }

2747 /** Process a EAP-Response/SIM-Challenge message - The response to our EAP-Request/SIM-Challenge message
2748  *
2749  * Verify that MAC, and RES match what we expect.
2750  */
2751 static unlang_action_t sim_challenge_response_process(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,
2752  request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)
2753 {
2754  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
2755  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
2756 
2757  uint8_t sres_cat[AKA_SIM_VECTOR_GSM_SRES_SIZE * 3];
2758  uint8_t *p = sres_cat;
2759 
2760  uint8_t calc_mac[AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE];
2761  ssize_t slen;
2762  fr_pair_t *mac;
2763  fr_pair_t *from_peer = request->request_pairs;
2764 
2765  memcpy(p, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.vector[0].sres, AKA_SIM_VECTOR_GSM_SRES_SIZE);
2766  p += AKA_SIM_VECTOR_GSM_SRES_SIZE;
2767  memcpy(p, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.vector[1].sres, AKA_SIM_VECTOR_GSM_SRES_SIZE);
2768  p += AKA_SIM_VECTOR_GSM_SRES_SIZE;
2769  memcpy(p, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.vector[2].sres, AKA_SIM_VECTOR_GSM_SRES_SIZE);
2770 
2771  mac = fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_mac);
2772  if (!mac) {
2773  REDEBUG("Missing AT_MAC attribute");
2774  failure:
2775  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2776  }
2777  if (mac->vp_length != AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE) {
2778  REDEBUG("MAC has incorrect length, expected %u bytes got %zu bytes",
2779  AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE, mac->vp_length);
2780  goto failure;
2781  }
2782 
2783  slen = fr_aka_sim_crypto_sign_packet(calc_mac, eap_session->this_round->response, true,
2784  eap_aka_sim_session->mac_md,
2785  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.k_aut, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.k_aut_len,
2786  sres_cat, sizeof(sres_cat));
2787  if (slen < 0) {
2788  RPEDEBUG("Failed calculating MAC");
2789  goto failure;
2790  } else if (slen == 0) {
2791  REDEBUG("Zero length AT_MAC attribute");
2792  goto failure;
2793  }
2794 
2795  if (memcmp(mac->vp_octets, calc_mac, sizeof(calc_mac)) == 0) {
2796  RDEBUG2("Received MAC matches calculated MAC");
2797  } else {
2798  REDEBUG("Received MAC does not match calculated MAC");
2799  RHEXDUMP_INLINE2(mac->vp_octets, AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE, "Received");
2800  RHEXDUMP_INLINE2(calc_mac, AKA_SIM_MAC_DIGEST_SIZE, "Expected");
2801  goto failure;
2802  }
2803 
2804  eap_aka_sim_session->challenge_success = true;
2805 
2806  /*
2807  * If the peer wants a Success notification, and
2808  * we included AT_RESULT_IND then send a success
2809  * notification, otherwise send a normal EAP-Success.
2810  */
2811  if (eap_aka_sim_session->send_result_ind) {
2812  if (!fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_result_ind)) {
2813  RDEBUG("We wanted to use protected result indications, but peer does not");
2814  eap_aka_sim_session->send_result_ind = false;
2815  } else {
2816  return common_success_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2817  }
2818  } else if (fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_result_ind)) {
2819  RDEBUG("Peer wanted to use protected result indications, but we do not");
2820  }
2821 
2822  return common_eap_success_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2823 }

2825 /** Process a EAP-Response/AKA-Identity message i.e. an EAP-AKA Identity-Response
2826  *
2827  * - If the message does not contain AT_IDENTITY, then enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
2828  * - If the user requested another identity, re-enter the AKA-Identity sate.
2829  * - ...or continue based on the value of &Identity-Type which was added by #aka_identity,
2830  * and possibly modified by the user.
2831  * - Fastauth - Enter the REAUTHENTICATION state.
2832  * - Pseudonym - Call 'load pseudonym { ... }'
2833  * - Permanent - Enter the CHALLENGE state.
2834  */
2835 static unlang_action_t aka_identity_response_process(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,
2836  request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)
2837 {
2838  eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t *inst = talloc_get_type_abort(mctx->instance, eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t);
2839  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
2840  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
2841  bool user_set_id_req;
2842  fr_pair_t *identity_type;
2843  fr_pair_t *from_peer = request->request_pairs;
2844  /*
2845  * Digest the identity response
2846  */
2847  if (eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_md) {
2848  if (fr_aka_sim_crypto_update_checkcode(eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_state,
2849  eap_session->this_round->response) < 0) {
2850  RPEDEBUG("Failed updating checkcode");
2851  failure:
2852  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2853  }
2854  }
2855 
2856  /*
2857  * See if the user wants us to request another
2858  * identity.
2859  *
2860  * If they set one themselves don't override
2861  * what they set.
2862  */
2863  user_set_id_req = identity_req_set_by_user(request, eap_aka_sim_session);
2864  if ((request->rcode == RLM_MODULE_NOTFOUND) || user_set_id_req) {
2865  if (!user_set_id_req) {
2866  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->last_id_req) {
2867  case AKA_SIM_ANY_ID_REQ:
2868  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_FULLAUTH_ID_REQ;
2869  break;
2870 
2871  case AKA_SIM_FULLAUTH_ID_REQ:
2872  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_PERMANENT_ID_REQ;
2873  break;
2874 
2875  case AKA_SIM_NO_ID_REQ: /* Should not happen */
2876  fr_assert(0);
2877  FALL_THROUGH;
2878 
2879  case AKA_SIM_PERMANENT_ID_REQ:
2880  REDEBUG("Peer sent no usable identities");
2881  goto failure;
2882 
2883  }
2884  RDEBUG2("Previous section returned (%s), requesting next most permissive identity (%s)",
2885  fr_table_str_by_value(rcode_table, request->rcode, "<INVALID>"),
2886  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_aka_sim_id_request_table, eap_aka_sim_session->id_req, "<INVALID>"));
2887  }
2888  return aka_identity_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2889  }
2890 
2891  /*
2892  * If the identity looks like a fast re-auth id
2893  * run fast re-auth, otherwise do fullauth.
2894  */
2895  identity_type = fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_identity_type);
2896  if (identity_type) switch (identity_type->vp_uint32) {
2897  case FR_IDENTITY_TYPE_VALUE_FASTAUTH:
2898  return common_reauthentication_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2899 
2900  /*
2901  * It's a pseudonym, which now needs resolving.
2902  * The resume function here calls aka_challenge_enter
2903  * if pseudonym resolution went ok.
2904  */
2905  case FR_IDENTITY_TYPE_VALUE_PSEUDONYM:
2906  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
2907  request,
2908  inst->actions.load_pseudonym,
2909  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
2910  pseudonym_load_resume,
2911  mod_signal,
2912  (void *)aka_challenge_enter);
2913  default:
2914  break;
2915  }
2916 
2917  return aka_challenge_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
2918 }

2920 /** Helper function to check for the presence and length of AT_SELECTED_VERSION and copy its value into the keys structure
2921  *
2922  * Also checks the version matches one of the ones we advertised in our version list,
2923  * which is a bit redundant seeing as there's only one version of EAP-SIM.
2924  */
2925 static int sim_start_selected_version_check(request_t *request, fr_pair_t *from_peer,
2926  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session)
2927 {
2928  fr_pair_t *selected_version_vp;
2929 
2930  /*
2931  * Check that we got an AT_SELECTED_VERSION
2932  */
2933  selected_version_vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_selected_version);
2934  if (!selected_version_vp) {
2935  REDEBUG("EAP-Response/SIM/Start does not contain AT_SELECTED_VERSION");
2936  return -1;
2937  }
2938 
2939  /*
2940  * See if the selected version was in our list
2941  */
2942  {
2943  uint8_t selected_version[2];
2944  uint8_t *p, *end;
2945  bool found = false;
2946 
2947  p = eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.version_list;
2948  end = p + eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.version_list_len;
2949 
2950  selected_version[0] = (selected_version_vp->vp_uint16 & 0xff00) >> 8;
2951  selected_version[1] = (selected_version_vp->vp_uint16 & 0x00ff);
2952 
2953  while (p < end) {
2954  if ((p[0] == selected_version[0]) && (p[1] == selected_version[1])) {
2955  found = true;
2956  /*
2957  * Update our keying material
2958  */
2959  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.version_select[0] = selected_version[0];
2960  eap_aka_sim_session->keys.gsm.version_select[1] = selected_version[1];
2961  break;
2962  }
2963  }
2964 
2965  if (!found) {
2966  REDEBUG("AT_SELECTED_VERSION (%u) does not match a value in our version list",
2967  selected_version_vp->vp_uint16);
2968  return -1;
2969  }
2970  }
2971 
2972  return 0;
2973 }

2979 static int sim_start_nonce_mt_check(request_t *request, fr_pair_t *from_peer,

3004 /** Process a EAP-Response/SIM-Start message i.e. an EAP-SIM Identity-Response
3005  *
3006  * - If the message does not contain AT_IDENTITY, then enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3007  * - If the user requested another identity, re-enter the SIM-START sate.
3008  * - ...or continue based on the value of &Identity-Type which was added by #sim_start,
3009  * and possibly modified by the user.
3010  * - Fastauth
3011  * - If AT_NONCE_MT or AT_SELECTED_VERSION are present, enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3012  * - ...or enter the REAUTHENTICATION state.
3013  * - Pseudonym - Verify selected version and AT_NONCE_MT, then call 'load pseudonym { ... }'
3014  * - Permanent - Verify selected version and AT_NONCE_MT, then enter the CHALLENGE state.
3015  */
3016 static unlang_action_t sim_start_response_process(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,
3017  request_t *request, eap_session_t *eap_session)
3018 {
3019  eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t *inst = talloc_get_type_abort(mctx->instance, eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t);
3020  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
3021  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
3022  bool user_set_id_req;
3023  fr_pair_t *identity_type;
3024 
3025  fr_pair_t *from_peer = request->request_pairs;
3026 
3027  /*
3028  * See if the user wants us to request another
3029  * identity.
3030  *
3031  * If they set one themselves don't override
3032  * what they set.
3033  */
3034  user_set_id_req = identity_req_set_by_user(request, eap_aka_sim_session);
3035  if ((request->rcode == RLM_MODULE_NOTFOUND) || user_set_id_req) {
3036  if (!user_set_id_req) {
3037  switch (eap_aka_sim_session->last_id_req) {
3038  case AKA_SIM_ANY_ID_REQ:
3039  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_FULLAUTH_ID_REQ;
3040  break;
3041 
3042  case AKA_SIM_FULLAUTH_ID_REQ:
3043  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_PERMANENT_ID_REQ;
3044  break;
3045 
3046  case AKA_SIM_NO_ID_REQ: /* Should not happen */
3047  fr_assert(0);
3048  FALL_THROUGH;
3049

3051  REDEBUG("Peer sent no usable identities");

3062  /*
3063  * If the identity looks like a fast re-auth id

3068  case FR_IDENTITY_TYPE_VALUE_FASTAUTH:
3069  /*

3071  *
3072  * The AT_NONCE_MT attribute MUST NOT be included if the AT_IDENTITY
3073  * with a fast re-authentication identity is present for fast
3074  * re-authentication

3076  if (fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_nonce_mt)) {

3251 /** Resume after 'recv Synchronization-Failure { ... }'
3252  *
3253  * - If 'recv Synchronization-Failure { ... }' returned a failure
3254  * rcode, enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3255  * - ...or if no 'recv Syncronization-Failure { ... }' section was
3256  * defined, then enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3257  * - ...or if the user didn't provide a new SQN value in &control.SQN
3258  * then enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3259  * - ...or enter the AKA-CHALLENGE state.
3260  */
3261 static unlang_action_t aka_synchronization_failure_recv_resume(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx,
3262  request_t *request, UNUSED void *rctx)
3263 {
3264  eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t *inst = talloc_get_type_abort(mctx->instance, eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t);
3265  eap_session_t *eap_session = eap_session_get(request->parent);
3266  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
3267  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
3268  fr_pair_t *vp;
3269 
3270  section_rcode_process(p_result, mctx,request, eap_session, eap_aka_sim_session);
3271 
3272  /*
3273  * If there's no section to handle this, then no resynchronisation
3274  * can't have occurred and we just send a reject.
3275  *
3276  * Similarly, if we've already received one synchronisation failure
3277  * then it's highly likely whatever user configured action was
3278  * configured was unsuccessful, and we should just give up.
3279  */
3280  if (!inst->actions.aka.recv_syncronization_failure || eap_aka_sim_session->prev_recv_sync_failure) {
3281  failure:
3282  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
3283  }
3284 
3285  /*
3286  * We couldn't generate an SQN and the user didn't provide one,
3287  * so we need to fail.
3288  */
3289  vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&request->control_pairs, attr_sim_sqn);
3290  if (!vp) {
3291  REDEBUG("No &control.SQN value provided after resynchronisation, cannot continue");
3292  goto failure;
3293  }
3294 
3295  /*
3296  * RFC 4187 Section #6.3.1
3297  *
3298  * "if the peer detects that the
3299  * sequence number in AUTN is not correct, the peer responds with
3300  * EAP-Response/AKA-Synchronization-Failure (Section 9.6), and the
3301  * server proceeds with a new EAP-Request/AKA-Challenge."
3302  */
3303  return aka_challenge_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
3304 }

3338 /** Decode the peer's response
3339  *
3340  * This is called by the state_* functions to decode the peer's response.
3341  */
3342 static unlang_action_t common_decode(fr_pair_t **subtype_vp, fr_pair_t **vps,
3343  rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request)
3344 {
3345  eap_session_t *eap_session = eap_session_get(request->parent);
3346  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
3347  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
3348 
3349  fr_aka_sim_decode_ctx_t ctx = {
3350  .keys = &eap_aka_sim_session->keys,
3351  };
3352  fr_pair_t *aka_vps;
3353  fr_cursor_t cursor;
3354 
3355  int ret;
3356 
3357  fr_cursor_init(&cursor, &request->request_pairs);
3358  fr_cursor_tail(&cursor);
3359 
3360  ret = fr_aka_sim_decode(request,
3361  &cursor,
3362  dict_eap_aka_sim,
3363  eap_session->this_round->response->type.data,
3364  eap_session->this_round->response->type.length,
3365  &ctx);
3366  /*
3367  * RFC 4187 says we *MUST* notify, not just
3368  * send an EAP-Failure in this case where
3369  * we cannot decode an EAP-AKA packet.
3370  */
3371  if (ret < 0) {
3372  RPEDEBUG2("Failed decoding attributes");
3373  failure:
3374  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
3375  }
3376  /* vps is the data from the client */
3377  aka_vps = fr_cursor_next(&cursor);
3378  if (aka_vps && RDEBUG_ENABLED2) {
3379  RDEBUG2("Decoded attributes");
3380  log_request_pair_list(L_DBG_LVL_2, request, aka_vps, NULL);
3381  }
3382 
3383  *subtype_vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&aka_vps, attr_eap_aka_sim_subtype);
3384  if (!*subtype_vp) {
3385  REDEBUG("Missing AT_SUBTYPE");
3386  goto failure;
3387  }
3388  *vps = aka_vps;
3389 
3390  RDEBUG2("Received EAP-Response/%pV", &(*subtype_vp)->data);
3391 
3392  RETURN_MODULE_OK;
3393 }

3407 /** FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state - Continue the state machine after receiving a response to our EAP-Request/(AKA|SIM)-Notification
3408  *
3409  * - Continue based on received AT_SUBTYPE value:
3410  * - EAP-Response/SIM-Client-Error - Call 'recv Failure-Notification-Ack { ... }'
3411  * - Anything else, enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3412  */
3413 static unlang_action_t common_failure_notification(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request)

3419  fr_pair_t *vps;
3420 
3421  common_decode(&subtype_vp, &vps, p_result, mctx, request);
3422  if (*p_result != RLM_MODULE_OK) return UNLANG_ACTION_CALCULATE_RESULT;
3423 
3424 #ifdef __clang_analyzer__
3425  if (!subtype_vp) {
3426  RETURN_MODULE_FAIL;
3427  }

3431  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_SIM_NOTIFICATION:

3433  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
3434  request,

3437  common_failure_notification_recv_resume,

3439  NULL);

3444  }

3477 /** REAUTHENTICATION state - Continue the state machine after receiving a response to our EAP-Request/SIM-Start
3478  *
3479  * - Continue based on received AT_SUBTYPE value:
3480  * - EAP-Response/(SIM|AKA)-Reauthentication - call 'recv Reauthentication-Response { ... }'
3481  * - EAP-Response/(SIM|AKA)-Client-Error - call 'recv Client-Error { ... }' and after that
3482  * send a EAP-Request/(SIM|AKA)-Notification indicating a General Failure.
3483  * - Anything else, enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3484  */
3485 static unlang_action_t common_reauthentication(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request)
3486 {
3487  eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t *inst = talloc_get_type_abort(mctx->instance, eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t);
3488  eap_session_t *eap_session = eap_session_get(request->parent);
3489  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
3490  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
3491 
3492  fr_pair_t *subtype_vp = NULL;
3493  fr_pair_t *from_peer;
3494 
3495  common_decode(&subtype_vp, &from_peer, p_result, mctx, request);
3496  if (*p_result != RLM_MODULE_OK) return UNLANG_ACTION_CALCULATE_RESULT;
3497 
3498 #ifdef __clang_analyzer__
3499  if (!subtype_vp) {
3500  RETURN_MODULE_FAIL;
3501  }
3502 #endif
3503  /*
3504  * These aren't allowed in Reauthentication responses as they don't apply:
3505  *
3506  * EAP_AKA_AUTHENTICATION_REJECT - We didn't provide an AUTN value
3507  * EAP_AKA_SYNCHRONIZATION_FAILURE - We didn't use new vectors.
3508  */
3509  switch (subtype_vp->vp_uint16) {
3510  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_SIM_REAUTHENTICATION:
3511  /*
3512  * AT_COUNTER_TOO_SMALL is handled
3513  * in common_reauthentication_response_process.
3514  */
3515  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
3516  request,
3517  inst->actions.recv_reauthentication_response,
3518  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
3519  common_reauthentication_response_recv_resume,
3520  mod_signal,
3521  NULL);
3522 
3523  /*
3524  * Case 1 where we're allowed to send an EAP-Failure
3525  */
3526  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_SIM_CLIENT_ERROR:
3527  client_error_debug(request, from_peer);
3528 
3529  eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted = false;
3530 
3531  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
3532  request,
3533  inst->actions.recv_client_error,
3534  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
3535  common_client_error_recv_resume,
3536  mod_signal,

3538

3541  * send an EAP-Failure in this case.
3542  */
3543  default:
3544  REDEBUG("Unexpected subtype %pV", &subtype_vp->data);
3545  eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted = false;
3546  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
3547  }
3548 }
