3550 /** AKA-CHALLENGE state - Continue the state machine after receiving a response to our EAP-Request/SIM-Challenge
3551  *
3552  * - Continue based on received AT_SUBTYPE value:
3553  * - EAP-Response/AKA-Challenge - call 'recv Challenge-Response { ... }'.
3554  * - EAP-Response/AKA-Authentication-Reject - call 'recv Authentication-Reject { ... }' and after that
3555  * send a EAP-Request/SIM-Notification indicating a General Failure.
3556  * - EAP-Response/AKA-Syncronization-Failure - call 'recv Syncronization-Failure { ... }'.
3557  * - EAP-Response/AKA-Client-Error - call 'recv Client-Error { ... }' and after that
3558  * send a EAP-Request/AKA-Notification indicating a General Failure.
3559  * - Anything else, enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3560  */
3561 static unlang_action_t aka_challenge(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request)
3562 {
3563  eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t *inst = talloc_get_type_abort(mctx->instance, eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t);
3564  eap_session_t *eap_session = eap_session_get(request->parent);
3565  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque, eap_aka_sim_session_t);
3566 
3567  fr_pair_t *subtype_vp = NULL;
3568  fr_pair_t *vp;
3569  fr_pair_t *from_peer;
3570 
3571  common_decode(&subtype_vp, &from_peer, p_result, mctx, request);
3572  if (*p_result != RLM_MODULE_OK) return UNLANG_ACTION_CALCULATE_RESULT;
3573 
3574 #ifdef __clang_analyzer__
3575  if (!subtype_vp) {
3576  RETURN_MODULE_FAIL;
3577  }
3578 #endif
3579 
3580  switch (subtype_vp->vp_uint16) {
3581  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_CHALLENGE:
3582  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
3583  request,
3584  inst->actions.recv_challenge_response,
3585  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
3586  aka_challenge_response_recv_resume,
3587  mod_signal,
3588  NULL);
3589 
3590  /*
3591  * Case 2 where we're allowed to send an EAP-Failure
3592  */
3593  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_AUTHENTICATION_REJECT:
3594  eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted = false;
3595 
3596  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
3597  request,
3598  inst->actions.aka.recv_authentication_reject,
3599  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
3600  aka_authentication_reject_recv_resume,
3601  mod_signal,
3602  NULL);
3603 
3604  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_SYNCHRONIZATION_FAILURE:
3605  {
3606  uint64_t new_sqn;
3607 
3608  eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted = false;
3609 
3610  vp = fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_auts);
3611  if (!vp) {
3612  REDEBUG("EAP-Response/AKA-Synchronisation-Failure missing AT_AUTS");
3613  failure:
3614  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
3615  }
3616 
3617  switch (fr_aka_sim_umts_resync_from_attrs(&new_sqn,
3618  request, vp, &eap_aka_sim_session->keys)) {
3619  /*
3620  * Add everything back that we'll need in the
3621  * next challenge round.
3622  */
3623  case 0:
3624  MEM(pair_add_control(&vp, attr_sim_sqn) >= 0);
3625  vp->vp_uint64 = new_sqn;
3626 
3627  MEM(pair_add_control(&vp, attr_sim_ki) >= 0);
3628  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.auc.ki,
3629  sizeof(eap_aka_sim_session->keys.auc.ki), false);
3630 
3631  MEM(pair_add_control(&vp, attr_sim_opc) >= 0);
3632  fr_pair_value_memdup(vp, eap_aka_sim_session->keys.auc.opc,
3633  sizeof(eap_aka_sim_session->keys.auc.opc), false);
3634  break;
3635 
3636  case 1: /* Don't have Ki or OPc so something else will need to deal with this */
3637  break;
3638 
3639  default:
3640  case -1:
3641  goto failure;
3642  }
3643 
3644  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
3645  request,
3646  inst->actions.aka.recv_syncronization_failure,
3647  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
3648  aka_synchronization_failure_recv_resume,
3649  mod_signal,
3650  NULL);
3651  }
3652 
3653  /*
3654  * Case 1 where we're allowed to send an EAP-Failure
3655  */
3656  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_SIM_CLIENT_ERROR:
3657  client_error_debug(request, from_peer);
3658 
3659  eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted = false;
3660 
3661  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
3662  request,
3663  inst->actions.recv_client_error,
3664  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
3665  common_client_error_recv_resume,
3666  mod_signal,
3667  NULL);
3668 
3669  /*
3670  * RFC 4187 says we *MUST* notify, not just
3671  * send an EAP-Failure in this case.
3672  */
3673  default:
3674  REDEBUG("Unexpected subtype %pV", &subtype_vp->data);
3675  eap_aka_sim_session->allow_encrypted = false;
3676  goto failure;
3677  }
3678 }

3746 /** AKA-IDENTITY state - Continue the state machine after receiving a response to our EAP-Request/AKA-Identity
3747  *
3748  * - Continue based on received AT_SUBTYPE value:
3749  * - EAP-Response/AKA-Identity - call either 'recv Identity-Response { ... }' or if
3750  * provided 'recv AKA-Identity-Response { ... }'. The idea here is that the
3751  * EAP-Identity-Response is really the first round in identity negotiation and
3752  * there's no real value distinguishing between the first round and subsequent
3753  * rounds, but if users do want to run different logic, then give them a way of
3754  * doing that.
3755  * - EAP-Response/AKA-Client-Error - call 'recv Client-Error { ... }' and after that
3756  * send a EAP-Request/SIM-Notification indicating a General Failure.
3757  * - Anything else, enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3758  */
3759 static unlang_action_t aka_identity(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request)
3760 {
3761  eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t *inst = talloc_get_type_abort(mctx->instance, eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t);
3762  eap_session_t *eap_session = eap_session_get(request->parent);
3763  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
3764  eap_aka_sim_session_t);
3765  fr_pair_t *subtype_vp = NULL;
3766  fr_pair_t *from_peer;
3767 
3768  common_decode(&subtype_vp, &from_peer, p_result, mctx, request);
3769  if (*p_result != RLM_MODULE_OK) return UNLANG_ACTION_CALCULATE_RESULT;
3770 
3771 #ifdef __clang_analyzer__
3772  if (!subtype_vp) {
3773  RETURN_MODULE_FAIL;
3774  }
3775 #endif
3776 
3777  switch (subtype_vp->vp_uint16) {
3778  /*
3779  * This is the subtype we expect
3780  */
3781  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_IDENTITY:
3782  {
3783  fr_pair_t *id;
3784  fr_aka_sim_id_type_t type;
3785 
3786  id = fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_identity);
3787  if (!id) {
3788  /*
3789  * 9.2. EAP-Response/Identity
3790  *
3791  * The peer sends EAP-Response/Identity in response to a valid
3792  * EAP-Request/Identity from the server.
3793  * The peer MUST include the AT_IDENTITY attribute. The usage of
3794  * AT_IDENTITY is defined in Section 4.1.
3795  */
3796  REDEBUG("EAP-Response/Identity does not contain AT_IDENTITY");
3797  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
3798  }
3799 
3800  /*
3801  * Add ID hint attributes to the request to help
3802  * the user make policy decisions.
3803  */
3804  identity_hint_pairs_add(&type, NULL, request, id->vp_strvalue);
3805  if (type == AKA_SIM_ID_TYPE_PERMANENT) {
3806  identity_to_permanent_identity(request, id,
3807  eap_aka_sim_session->type,
3808  inst->strip_permanent_identity_hint);
3809  }
3810 
3811  /*
3812  * Update cryptographic identity
3813  */
3814  identity_to_crypto_identity(request, eap_aka_sim_session,
3815  (uint8_t const *)id->vp_strvalue, id->vp_length);
3816 
3817  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
3818  request,
3819  inst->actions.aka.recv_aka_identity_response?
3820  inst->actions.aka.recv_aka_identity_response:
3821  inst->actions.recv_identity_response,
3822  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
3823  aka_identity_response_recv_resume,
3824  mod_signal,
3825  NULL);
3826  }
3827 
3828  /*
3829  * Case 1 where we're allowed to send an EAP-Failure
3830  *
3831  * This can happen in the case of a conservative
3832  * peer, where it refuses to provide the permanent
3833  * identity.
3834  */
3835  case FR_SUBTYPE_VALUE_AKA_SIM_CLIENT_ERROR:
3836  client_error_debug(request, from_peer);
3837 
3838  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
3839  request,
3840  inst->actions.recv_client_error,
3841  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
3842  common_client_error_recv_resume,
3843  mod_signal,
3844  NULL);
3845 
3846  default:
3847  /*
3848  * RFC 4187 says we *MUST* notify, not just
3849  * send an EAP-Failure in this case.
3850  */
3851  REDEBUG("Unexpected subtype %pV", &subtype_vp->data);
3852  return common_failure_notification_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
3853  }
3854 }

3965 /** Resume after 'recv Identity-Response { ... }'
3966  *
3967  * - Perform the majority of eap_aka_sim_session_t initialisation.
3968  * - If 'recv Identity-Response { ... }' returned a failure rcode, enter the FAILURE-NOTIFICATION state.
3969  * - ...or continue based on the identity hint byte in the AT_IDENTITY value or EAP-Identity-Response value:
3970  * - If identity is a pseudonym, call load pseudonym { ... }.
3971  * - If identity is a fastauth identity, enter the REAUTHENTICATE state.
3972  * - If identity is a permanent identity, enter the CHALLENGE state.
3973  */
3974 static unlang_action_t common_eap_identity_resume(rlm_rcode_t *p_result, module_ctx_t const *mctx, request_t *request, UNUSED void *rctx)
3975 {
3976  eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t *inst = talloc_get_type_abort(mctx->instance, eap_aka_sim_common_conf_t);
3977  eap_session_t *eap_session = eap_session_get(request->parent);
3978  eap_aka_sim_session_t *eap_aka_sim_session = talloc_get_type_abort(eap_session->opaque,
3979  eap_aka_sim_session_t);

3981  fr_aka_sim_method_hint_t running, hinted;
3982  fr_pair_t *from_peer = request->request_pairs;
3983 
3984  section_rcode_process(p_result, mctx,request, eap_session, eap_aka_sim_session);
3985

3987  * Ignore attempts to change the EAP-Type
3988  * This must be done before we enter
3989  * the submodule.
3990  */
3991  eap_type = fr_pair_find_by_da(&request->control_pairs, attr_eap_type);
3992  if (eap_type) RWDEBUG("Ignoring &control.EAP-Type, this must be set *before* the EAP module is called");

3995

3997  * Set default configuration, we may allow these
3998  * to be toggled by attributes later.
3999  */
4000  eap_aka_sim_session->send_result_ind = inst->protected_success;
4001  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_NO_ID_REQ; /* Set the default */
4002 
4003  /*
4004  * Unless AKA-Prime is explicitly disabled,
4005  * use it... It has stronger keying, and
4006  * binds authentication to the network.
4007  */
4008  switch (eap_session->type) {
4009  case FR_EAP_METHOD_SIM:
4010  RDEBUG2("New EAP-SIM session");
4011 
4012  running = AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_SIM;
4013 
4014  eap_aka_sim_session->type = FR_EAP_METHOD_SIM;
4015  eap_aka_sim_session->mac_md = EVP_sha1(); /* no checkcode support, so no checkcode_md */
4016 
4017  /*
4018  * RFC 5448 makes no mention of being
4019  * able to use this with EAP-SIM, so it's
4020  * permanently disabled for that EAP method.
4021  */
4022  eap_aka_sim_session->send_at_bidding_prefer_prime = false;
4023  break;
4024 
4025  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA:
4026  RDEBUG2("New EAP-AKA session");
4027 
4028  running = AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_AKA;
4029 
4030  eap_aka_sim_session->type = FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA;
4031  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_md = eap_aka_sim_session->mac_md = EVP_sha1();
4032  eap_aka_sim_session->send_at_bidding_prefer_prime = inst->send_at_bidding_prefer_prime;
4033  break;
4034 
4035  case FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME:
4036  RDEBUG2("New EAP-AKA' session");
4037 
4038  running = AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_AKA_PRIME;
4039 
4040  eap_aka_sim_session->type = FR_EAP_METHOD_AKA_PRIME;
4041  eap_aka_sim_session->kdf = FR_KDF_VALUE_PRIME_WITH_CK_PRIME_IK_PRIME;
4042  eap_aka_sim_session->checkcode_md = eap_aka_sim_session->mac_md = EVP_sha256();
4043  break;
4044 
4045  default:
4046  fr_assert(0);
4047  RETURN_MODULE_FAIL;
4048  }
4049 
4050  /*
4051  * Warn the user if the selected identity
4052  * does not match what's hinted.
4053  */
4054  if (method) {
4055  switch (method->vp_uint32) {
4056  case FR_METHOD_HINT_VALUE_AKA_PRIME:
4057  hinted = AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_AKA_PRIME;
4058  break;
4059 
4060  case FR_METHOD_HINT_VALUE_AKA:
4061  hinted = AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_AKA;
4062  break;
4063 
4064  case FR_METHOD_HINT_VALUE_SIM:
4065  hinted = AKA_SIM_METHOD_HINT_SIM;
4066  break;
4067 
4068  default:
4069  hinted = running;
4070  break;
4071  }
4072

4074  RWDEBUG("EAP-Identity hints that EAP-%s should be started, but we're attempting EAP-%s",
4075  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_aka_sim_id_method_table, hinted, "<INVALID>"),
4076  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_aka_sim_id_method_table, running, "<INVALID>"));
4077  }
4078  }
4079 
4080  /*
4081  * We always start by requesting any ID
4082  * initially as we can always negotiate down.
4083  */
4084  if (!identity_req_set_by_user(request, eap_aka_sim_session)) {
4085  if (request->rcode == RLM_MODULE_NOTFOUND) {
4086  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = AKA_SIM_ANY_ID_REQ;
4087  RDEBUG2("Previous section returned (%s), requesting additional identity (%s)",
4088  fr_table_str_by_value(rcode_table, request->rcode, "<INVALID>"),
4089  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_aka_sim_id_request_table, eap_aka_sim_session->id_req, "<INVALID>"));
4090  } else if (inst->request_identity != AKA_SIM_NO_ID_REQ) {
4091  eap_aka_sim_session->id_req = inst->request_identity;
4092  RDEBUG2("Requesting additional identity (%s)",
4093  fr_table_str_by_value(fr_aka_sim_id_request_table, eap_aka_sim_session->id_req, "<INVALID>"));
4094  }
4095  }
4096 
4097  /*
4098  * User may want us to always request an identity
4099  * initially. The RFCs says this is also the
4100  * better way to operate, as the supplicant
4101  * can 'decorate' the identity in the identity
4102  * response.
4103  */
4104  if (eap_aka_sim_session->id_req != AKA_SIM_NO_ID_REQ) return common_identity_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
4105 
4106  /*
4107  * If the identity looks like a fast re-auth id
4108  * run fast re-auth, otherwise do a fullauth.
4109  */
4110  identity_type = fr_pair_find_by_da(&from_peer, attr_eap_aka_sim_identity_type);
4111  if (identity_type) switch (identity_type->vp_uint32) {
4112  case FR_IDENTITY_TYPE_VALUE_FASTAUTH:
4113  return common_reauthentication_enter(p_result, mctx, request, eap_session);
4114 
4115  /*
4116  * It's a pseudonym, which now needs resolving.
4117  * The resume function here calls aka_challenge_enter
4118  * if pseudonym resolution went ok.
4119  */
4120  case FR_IDENTITY_TYPE_VALUE_PSEUDONYM:
4121  return unlang_module_yield_to_section(p_result,
4122  request,
4123  inst->actions.load_pseudonym,
4124  RLM_MODULE_NOOP,
4125  pseudonym_load_resume,
4126  mod_signal,
4127  (void *)common_challenge_enter);
4128 
4129  case FR_IDENTITY_TYPE_VALUE_PERMANENT:
4130  FALL_THROUGH;
4131 
4132  default:
4133  break;
4134  }
4135

4137 }
